AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1431* House Bill No. 1409
by adding the following as a new, appropriately designated item at the end of Section 60:
Item __. In the fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, from the $145,920,000 recurring
appropriation made in Section 1 of Chapter 4, Public Acts of 2025 (Senate Bill 5 / House Bill 5)
(1st Extraordinary Session), for the sole purpose of implementing Senate Bill 1 / House Bill 4,
relative to Education Freedom Scholarships, the amount of such appropriation is instead hereby
transferred and appropriated to the Department of Human Services for the sole purpose of
providing a grant (nonrecurring) to each working-age resident of this state who earns an income
that is less than the state's median income, based on the most recent calculations by the United
States Census Bureau. Each grant is capped in the amount of $10,000 per eligible recipient.
